    "causal_summary": "Phase 001 shipped the deep-context loop as a host-driven consumer of `deep-loop-runtime`, but it skipped the runtime's durability and validation layer that `deep-research` and `deep-review` already rely on. This phase brings deep-context to robustness parity by wiring five runtime features into the host-driven loop, every one gated to `loop_type='context'` so research and review behavior is untouched: crash-safe atomic state writes, corrupt-tail JSONL recovery, seat-output validation before merge, single-writer loop locking, and a CLI-dispatch recursion guard. Two further runtime features were evaluated and excluded as non-gaps with recorded rationale.",
